I think the battery hack might actually work but the problem with Lia was that she didn't care about the shape of the foil and just cut it in a square. If you cut it the way they did it, the middle part will be more narrow and the electrons that will have to go through will have to more like crowded and that will cause more friction. The made friction will get the part hotter and hotter and it should burn.

If you don't exactly understand what the narrow part does you can imagine it as a tunnel. If the middle part of a tunnel would be more narrow than the others the vehicles would slow down and create a crowd. They flow fastly in the beginning and the end but in the middle they almost stop and with the elecrons is almost the same but cars don't create friction. The electrons want to go forward so fast that they crash and create the explosion that might be the fire Lia was looking for.

Therefore the hack may work but you need to watch for the shape of the foil.

Thanks to everyone that decided to take their time to read all this!
(I am sorry for any mistakes kn my English as it is not my first language)
:)

snippet.textDisplay:
He clutched her wrists and examined her, cautiously checking for any signs of harm. This simple action started the process. A surge of electricity shot through them both, as the pulling sensation returned to their chests. Malayjah closed her eyes and allowed the strength of the bond to have it's way with her. Zy'Phon had to bite down on his tongue to keep himself from squirming uncontrollably. The feeling was no doubt a pleasurable one, but that pleasure came with massive amounts of pain. Zy'Phon, who had a body more durable than Malayjah's inhaled deeply as the pain cascaded through him. Malayjah let out several cries of agony.The young demon in front of her felt excruciating discomfort at the sound of it. Once the bond calmed itself, Zy'Phon loosened his grip on Malayjah.

Without letting go of her wrists he kneeled before her, gazing straight into those big brown eyes. "I am now your faithful guardian. I promise to protect you until the day I die. I will be loyal to you and only you."
